<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-6593] TextRecordInputStream doesn&apos;t close SequenceFile.Reader</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6593</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using hadoop fs -text on a glob with many sequence files can fail with too many open file handles.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cause seems to be that TextRecordInputStream doesn&apos;t override close(), so printToStdout&apos;s call to close doesn&apos;t release the SequenceFile.Reader.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
